trans-unit.source: Implements an accessible object that <xref href="System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.CompositeActivityDesigner"></xref> classes use to adjust the designer user interface for users who have impairments.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.CompositeDesignerAccessibleObject"></xref> class by using the specified <xref href="System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.CompositeActivityDesigner"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.CompositeActivityDesigner"></xref> to apply to the accessible object.
Returns the child accessible object associated with the activity designer at the specified index location.
The zero-based index of the child accessible object.
An <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleObject"></xref> associated with the child <xref href="System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.ActivityDesigner"></xref> at the specified index location.
Returns the number of child accessible objects that belong to the <xref href="System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.CompositeDesignerAccessibleObject"></xref>.
The number of children that belong to the <xref href="System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.CompositeDesignerAccessibleObject"></xref>.
Gets the accessible state of the current <xref href="System.Workflow.ComponentModel.Design.CompositeDesignerAccessibleObject"></xref>.

State has the following possible values: <xref:System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleStates>, <xref:System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleStates>, <xref:System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleStates>, <xref:System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleStates>, <xref:System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleStates>, <xref:System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleStates>, <xref:System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleStates>, <xref:System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleStates>, <xref:System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleStates>, and <xref:System.Windows.Forms.AccessibleStates>.
